# eGymSystem.Frontend Structure Rule

Apply in `eGymSystem.Frontend/src` with this structure:

- `app/modules/<area>/...` -> pages, feature components, area routing/module files
- `app/api-services/<feature>/` -> `<feature>-api.service.ts` + `<feature>-api.models.ts`
- `app/core/` -> interceptors, cross-cutting services, helpers
- `app/modules/shared/` -> reusable UI/shared module/material bundles

Generation rules:

- For backend endpoint integration, add/update feature API service first.
- API service naming: `<feature>-api.service.ts`; models colocated in same feature folder.
- Use Angular style already in repo (`inject(HttpClient)`, `providedIn: 'root'`).
- Keep module pattern filenames already used: `*-module.ts`, `*-routing-module.ts`.
- Components stay in feature folders with triplet files (`.component.ts/.html/.scss`) when present.
- Reuse existing interceptors/error flow; do not duplicate auth/error plumbing inside components.
- Use shared UI utilities/components before creating new duplicates.
- Do not create/edit files in `Market.Frontend`; frontend target is `eGymSystem.Frontend` only.
